In a message dated 4/2/01 10:28:46 AM Mountain Daylight Time,
Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< Of course, some children just feel things more intensely and aren't we
glad we homeschool them! >>


Definitely I couldn't imagine my dd in school. I barely made it through,
but I am scared from it too. I do not use commercial cleaners in my home as I
am sensitive to them myself. We eat 90% organic and very few processed foods.
She can easily concentrate on things but is wired all day long. Exhausting.

NICKI~
